hands_on_practices.solution:
1. Polariton dispersion relation:  
   $$k^2 c^2 = \omega^2 \epsilon(\omega)$$

2. Thus  
   $$k = \frac{\omega}{c}\sqrt{\epsilon(\omega)}$$  
   and the momentum is  
   $$p = \hbar k = \frac{\hbar \omega}{c}\sqrt{\epsilon(\omega)}$$

3. Dielectric function for one TO mode:  
   $$\epsilon(\omega)
     =\epsilon_{\infty} \frac{\omega_{LO}^2-\omega^2}{\omega_{TO}^2-\omega^2}$$

4. Lyddane–Sachs–Teller relation:
   $$\frac{\omega_{LO}^2}{\omega_{TO}^2}=\frac{\epsilon_{st}}{\epsilon_{\infty}}
   \quad\Longrightarrow\quad
   \omega_{LO}^2=\omega_{TO}^2\frac{\epsilon_{st}}{\epsilon_{\infty}}$$

5. Evaluate at $\omega=\omega_{TO}/2$:
   $$\omega^2=\frac{\omega_{TO}^2}{4},$$
   $$\omega_{LO}^2-\omega^2
     =\omega_{TO}^2\frac{\epsilon_{st}}{\epsilon_{\infty}}
      -\frac{\omega_{TO}^2}{4}
     =\omega_{TO}^2\left(\frac{\epsilon_{st}}{\epsilon_{\infty}}-\frac14\right),$$
   $$\omega_{TO}^2-\omega^2
     =\omega_{TO}^2-\frac{\omega_{TO}^2}{4}
     =\frac{3\omega_{TO}^2}{4}$$

6. Hence
   $$\epsilon\left(\frac{\omega_{TO}}{2}\right)
     =\epsilon_{\infty}
      \frac{\omega_{TO}^2\left(\frac{\epsilon_{st}}{\epsilon_{\infty}}-\frac14\right)}
           {\frac{3\omega_{TO}^2}{4}}
     =\epsilon_{\infty}\frac{4}{3}\left(\frac{\epsilon_{st}}{\epsilon_{\infty}}-\frac14\right)
     =\frac{4\epsilon_{st}-\epsilon_{\infty}}{3}$$

7. Finally,
   $$p
     =\frac{\hbar \omega}{c}\sqrt{\epsilon(\omega)}
     =\frac{\hbar (\omega_{TO}/2)}{c}
      \sqrt{\frac{4\epsilon_{st}-\epsilon_{\infty}}{3}}
     =\frac{\hbar \omega_{TO}}{2c}
      \sqrt{\frac{4\epsilon_{st}-\epsilon_{\infty}}{3}}$$
